Business Brief -- Compression Labs Inc.:
   Videoconference Gear Maker
   Posts 4th-Quarter Net Loss
The charges resulted in a net loss of $17.7 million, or
$1.62 a share, compared with year-earlier net income of $1.2
million, or 13 cents a share. Revenue rose 28% to $21.5
million from $16.8 million.
   Compression Labs said its base videoconferencing business
is rapidly moving toward software-based products and away
from hardware, prompting the write-down of assets. The
company said it sees its sales moving to high-volume,
lower-cost products.
   For the year, Compression Labs posted a net loss of $15.1
million, or $1.55 a share, on revenue of $72.6 million. In
1990, it had net income of $2.6 million, or 27 cents a share,
on revenue of $51.8 million.